fine_print:
* This question pertains only to the US federal government. For purposes of this question, "changing the name" is defined as the Gulf of Mexico being [standardized](https://blogs.loc.gov/law/2024/09/charting-the-course-what-is-the-u-s-board-on-geographic-names/) differently in usage across the US government. Whether US states, other countries, or any other entities such as mapmakers follow suit in renaming the Gulf of Mexico has no effect on resolution.
* The US federal government's renaming of the Gulf of Mexico need not take effect before April 1, 2025. This question resolves based on an official announcement.&#x20;
* Vague statements such as President Trump, his press secretary or other officials saying that this is favored or desired in the future will not be considered a valid announcement. For purposes of this question, a renaming announcement will count only when it is announced in a manner in which there is authority to enact the name change.&#x20;
* Because this question resolves based solely on an announcement, legal challenges will not affect resolution of this question.
